<p>i am using a for loop to generate paragraph tags based on the length of my <code>array</code>. I want each of these p tags generated to have the same <code>innerHTML</code>. I can get the tags to generate with the class name but the <code>innerHTML</code> remains <strong>blank</strong>. </p>  <p>I have tried the following to no avail, not sure what I am doing wrong.</p>  <pre><code>for (i = 0; i &lt; numArray.length; i++) {        var line = document.createElement("p");      line.className = "line";      document.body.appendChild(line);       var b = document.getElementsByClassName("line");      b.innerHTML = "|";   } </code></pre>